  "prompt": "How do you factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer?",
  "response": "To factory reset an iPhone 4 without using a computer, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Backup Your Data**: Before you proceed, ensure you back up any important data, as a factory reset will erase everything on the device.\n\n2. **Go to Settings**: Unlock your iPhone and tap on the **Settings** app (the gear icon).\n\n3. **Select General**: Scroll down and tap on **General**.\n\n4. **Reset Options**: Scroll to the bottom and tap on **Reset**.\n\n5. **Erase All Content and Settings**: Tap on **Erase All Content and Settings**. You may need to enter your passcode to proceed.\n\n6. **Confirm**: A warning message will appear explaining that this action will delete all media and data. Confirm that you want to proceed by tapping on **Erase iPhone**.\n\n7. **Wait for Reset**: Your iPhone will now begin the factory reset process. This may take a few minutes. Once complete, your iPhone will restart and display the initial setup screen.\n\nAfter the reset, you can set up your iPhone as new or restore it from a backup if you have one.",
